metadata.name: The Massive Minar
metadata.description:
Qutub Minar is a World Heritage site, having a minaret that is 72.5m high, and is the tallest brick minaret in the World. The Qutub Minar glows to its beauty in the evening with specially placed lights. The Qutub complex is not just known for having the tallest brick Minar in the world but it also houses ASHOKA PILLAR which is also called the Iron pillar of Delhi. 

In this image, the tallest brick Minar of the World has been captured in a distinctive frame to create a different perspective and a new dimension to explore the place.

Artist: Sachin Ghai
Medium: Photography
Edition: 1/1
Size: 3840 x 2880
